{
  "texts": [
    "Overall, our evaluation includes six vanilla imputers (MICE, OT-Impute, SoftImpute, GAIN, MIWAE, TabCSDI), three sampling-based variants (GAIN-S, MIWAE-S, TabCSDI-S), and two uncertainty-output models (GAIN-U, MIWAE-U).",
    "Each yields an estimated predictive distribution P(x mis ij | X obs, M) for every missing cell-either empirically from multiple imputations or parametrically from model outputswhich we evaluate in terms of accuracy and calibration.",
    "B. Benchmarking DataWe use five numerical tabular datasets spanning sizes and dimensionalities (Table I).",
    "All features are z-scored to stabilize training and ensure comparable error scales.Dataset #Rec.",
    "housing 20,640 8 biodegradation 1055 41 cancer 569 30 energy 768 8 wine 178 13TABLE I: Dataset statistics."
  ]
}